\n<Suspicious Man>This town has a church that doesn't quite fit in, a grand
one at that. Seems it was built with the money from those
higher-ups. If they have that kind of money, they should be
handing out food instead, damn hypocrites.

\n<Suspicious Man>Oops, maybe I'll be punished for saying such things... If
faith could fill one's stomach, I'd pray for a lifetime.

\n<Suspicious Man>"With the sister gone, this church is finished, huh? Or will
someone else come to take her place, I wonder?"

\n<Suspicious Man>Necromancy or whatever is fine, but just make sure to
properly dispose of the corpses. They're the most
troublesome kind of trash after all.

\n<Suspicious Man>I may think faith can go to hell, but cemeteries do serve a
purpose. Maybe I'll make a donation once in a while.

\n<Believer?>By offering prayers, you can gradually remove the black mold
that spreads in your heart. Come now, you must also pray.

\n<Katara>(While making a gesture of prayer, they're squinting their
eyes open, searching for something. It seems like they're
scoping out something to steal...)

\n<Believer?>I knew it was suspicious. Such a grand church like this.
Let's steal what we can while we still have the chance.

\n<Believer?>I thought I might find something to steal passing by, but I
was truly moved by the Sister's earnestness. Seriously, who
is it? Who's the scumbag spreading those awful rumors?

\n<Believer>At first, I didn't think we needed a church, but having
someone to perform services for the dead and manage the
cemetery is a relief. If bodies are left as they are, they
can spread disease.

\n<Believer>And the sister is such a good person. She listens to our
troubles with compassion, she's gentle and pure-hearted.
Talking to her feels like it cleanses your own soul.

\n<Follower>I still can't believe that Soel-san was tampering with a
corpse. I wonder if there was a reason for it.

\n<Follower>No, even if there was a reason, it's not acceptable.
Perhaps... she was already broken inside when she came here.

\n<Follower>Even though they've been taking care of the graves, to be
accused of necromancy... It's a cruel rumor to spread. Poor
Sister... Who would do such a thing...
\n<Katara>(It's me! It's me! It's not a rumor... Ugh...)

\n<Katara>(A rumor, huh... Maybe it was better for these people this
way...)

\n<Believer?>Soel-chan is amazing, isn't she?♥ She has the air of a pure
lady, yet those breasts are something else. It's no wonder
people come to pray.
\n<Believer?>Makes you want to offer something up, right?
\n<Katara>Offer what?

\n<Believer?>Huh? Where's Soel-chan? Hey, I came to see Soel-chan. Do you
know where they went? Do they have a day off or something?

\n<Believer?>Poor Soel-chan, being the subject of such weird rumors. I
don't know if they're true or not, but hey, you can play
with my corpse as much as you want. Hehe♥
\n<Katara>Gross! (You can keep it by your side when you're dead...)

\n<Katara>(Even if they knew her true identity, this person probably
wouldn't care...)

\n<Follower>I'm of the lightning and water elements, so there's no
church for me. Churches only exist for the mixed attributes
of fire-water, fire-lightning, water-wind, and wind-
lightning.

\n<Follower>Hey little one, you're fire and wind, right? You must have
your own struggles too.

\n<Follower>Well, elements and such aren't the essence of a person. It's
not about birth but experience. "It's how you live your
life," my grandpa always said. He's dead now though.

\n<Follower>The sister has been captured. Well, I've lost my old man
too, and I can't count how many times I've wished he could
come back to life.

\n<Follower>Those obsessed with necromancy must have someone they
desperately wanted to bring back to life, I suppose. But I
don't know.

\n<Follower>"It must be some nasty rumor that the Sister is using

\n<Follower>"Ah, the very picture of innocence. You can tell when you've
lived as long as I have. She's not a bad child."
